# Bug: dependency-cycle diagnostics underline the whole first task.
#
# `analysis/diagnostics.go:dependencyCycles` anchors on
# `symbols.Task(cycle[0]).Position` — fine for picking the report
# site, but it spans the whole task. A reader gets a fat underline
# across the body without seeing which dep edge actually closes
# the cycle. Narrowing to the offending dep token in the dep list
# would point at the real culprit.
#
# Expected: underline on the dep edge that closes the cycle (e.g.
# the `a` in `task c => a`).
# Actual: the entire `task a { ... }` block underlines.

task a => b {
    echo a
}

task b => c {
    echo b
}

task c => a {
    echo c
}
